Interpreting P-values

  • The reading of medical journals today presupposes considerable statistical knowledge; however, those doctors who are not familiar with statistical theory tend to interpret the results of significance tests uncritically or even incorrectly [1]. Same can be said for the use of clinical decision support systems.
  • P-values are only interpretable in the context of the specific hypothesis being tested and in the context of signficance levels. 5% has no scientific meaning, but has become a de-facto standard.
